      "side": 1,
      "message": "fyi, there is no need for quotes in direct assignment per Posix, i.e.:\n\n  FOO\u003d$BAR\n\nwill always do the correct thing, even if $BAR contains space. On the other hand, with:\n\n  local FOO\u003d$BAR\n\nThe result depends on the shell. Some of them consider \u0027local\u0027 to be a command, and the you would need to quote \"$BAR\" to make it work properly. Crazy, I know.",
      "revId": "135028165648c8339e3cce5d9f7d941d02c8752e",
